  Setting Up ChatGPT and Idea Generation

In this video, we're going to take a look at ChatGPT as a creative concept generation tool and compare it to other helpful tools on the market. I'll show you specific ways in which you can use ChatGPT to unlock hidden creative ideas and I'll even show you how to develop a creative mentor.

Our Favorite LLMs (Large Language Models)

ChatGPT (Our Favorite)

Pros:

  • Most creative language from extensive testing
  • Can generate images directly in the chat
  • Can be trained on your data very easily
  • Ability to create AutoGPTs
  • First-Movers Advantage

Cons:

  • Has content restrictions that can limit creativity on mature themes.
  • Costs a bit of money each month for the best version.

Google Gemini (Bard)

Pros:

  • Can reference Google's knowledge base very quickly
  • Is free
  • Pretty darn creative

Cons:

  • Language is less natural
  • More challenging to train on your information
  • More restricted than ChatGPT

Claude

Pros:

  • Creative
  • Easy to Use
  • Can Be Trained on a Lot of Data

Cons:

  • The Least Creative Tool on This List
